    "headline": "ADI Q1 Deep Dive: Industrial, Data Center, and Power Portfolio Drive Revenue Upside Amid Market Caution",
    "summary": "Manufacturer of analog chips Analog Devices (NASDAQ:ADI) reported Q1 CY2026 results beating Wall Street’s revenue expectations, with sales up 37.2% year on year to $3.62 billion. On top of that, next quarter’s revenue guidance ($3.9 billion at the midpoint) was surprisingly good and 8.1% above what analysts were expecting. Its non-GAAP profit of $3.09 per share was 6.2% above analysts’ consensus estimates.",
